{
  "text": "Kobayashi et al. showed a significant improvement in shoulder subluxation with FES of the deltoid and supraspinatus muscles [CITATION_1] . Although segmental muscle force had also increased, the results were not statistically significant. Linn et al. report the effectiveness of FES in preventing GHS, but the effects of the treatment were not maintained at 4 and 12 weeks [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
